headline: After He Sold His First Company, Elon Musk Chose A McLaren F1 Instead Of A House. The Choice Ties Directly To The Elusive Tesla Roadster
summary: When Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA) CEO Elon Musk sold his first company, Zip2, for more than $300 million in 1999, he suddenly had enough cash to buy just about anything. Faced with a choice of buying a house or buying a car, he went with the car. But not just any car, the ultra-rare McLaren F1. headline: PayPal’s New CEO And Embedded Payments Push Challenge Depressed Valuation
summary: PayPal Holdings (NasdaqGS:PYPL) has appointed Enrique Lores, former President and CEO of HP Inc., as its new CEO. The company is expanding embedded payments through new integrations with UpdatePromise for automotive service payments and Authvia for text based transactions. These moves reflect a push to make PayPal and Venmo more central to everyday digital commerce experiences.
